{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:42.166059+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e0f90ac88e1236616df18600c7f7a5f80ac113c6)", "id": "lc_748a0837-0e9b-4320-be3c-c4e8691c4a5d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nfrom fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer\nfrom jose import jwt\n\nfrom app.services import BaseService\nfrom app.settings import settings\n\n# for authentication that works seamlessly with OpenAPI\nreuseable_oauth = OAuth2PasswordBearer(\n    tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\",\n    scheme_name=\"JWT\"\n)\n\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Creates a hash of the password\"\"\"\n    hashed_password = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.hash(password)\n    return hashed_password\n\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Checks if a password corresponds to a hash\"\"\"\n    password_is_verified = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.verify(\n        plain_password, hashed_password\n    )\n\n    return bool(password_is_verified)\n\n\ndef create_auth_token(payload: Dict[str, Any], expiry: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    This handles the encoding of user information into a token\n    that can be used. It is generic so as to accomodate access and\n    refresh token.\n    \"\"\"\n    expiry_delta = datetime.now() + timedelta(seconds=expiry)\n    data_to_encode = {\"expiry\": str(expiry_delta), \"data\": payload}\n    encoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n        data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n    )\n\n    return encoded_data\n\n\nclass UserService(BaseService):\n    \"\"\"\n    This class helps perform bulk of activities required by the corresponding API\n    \"\"\"\n    def a_method(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Here, the use of `self.save` is demonstrated.\n        Ensure to take out this method.\n        \"\"\"\n        model_instance = ...\n        self.save(model_instance)", "id": "lc_7b7e6d25-ed5e-4c6b-a668-e28c8972b70f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "51324f9a-d878-48f3-8e67-1efb8e56cba5", "tool_call_id": "call_f1d613580b7b496da0c9ddd1", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:52:08.763335+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "In this template, application settings are derived from environment variables through a centralized `Settings` class that reads raw environment variables, computes composite values, and provides constants. Here's how each category works:\n\n## 1. **Raw Environment Variables**\nThe `.example.env` file defines the raw variables:\n```env\nPOSTGRES_USER=sasori\nPOSTGRES_PASSWORD=sasori\nPOSTGRES_DB=akatsuki\nPOSTGRES_TEST_DB=hebi\nPOSTGRES_PORT=5432\nPOSTGRES_HOST=postgres\nREDIS_HOST=redis\nREDIS_PORT=6379\nSECRET_KEY=meandyouaretogether\nDEBUG=True\nPORT=11000\nALLOWED_HOST=0.0.0.0\n```\n\n## 2. **Settings Class (`app/settings.py`)**\nThe `Settings` class reads these using `os.environ.get()` and maps them to internal attributes:\n\n```python\nclass Settings:\n    ALLOWED_HOST = environ.get(\"ALLOWED_HOST\")\n    SECRET_KEY = environ.get(\"SECRET_KEY\")\n    DEBUG = bool(environ.get(\"DEBUG\"))\n    ALLOWED_PORT = int(environ.get(\"PORT\"))\n    DB_USER = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_USER\")\n    DB_PASSWORD = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PASSWORD\")\n    DB_DB = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_DB\")\n    DB_PORT = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PORT\")\n    DB_HOST = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_HOST\")\n    TEST_DB = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_TEST_DB\")\n    REDIS_HOST = environ.get(\"REDIS_HOST\", \"localhost\")\n    REDIS_PORT = environ.get(\"REDIS_PORT\", \"6379\")\n```\n\n## 3. **Database URLs (Derived)**\nThe class constructs PostgreSQL connection URLs by interpolating the individual environment variables:\n\n```python\nDB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{DB_DB}\"\nTEST_DB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{TEST_DB}\"\n```\n\nThese URLs are then used in `app/db.py` to create database connections and engines.\n\n## 4. **Token Settings (Hardcoded Constants + Environment Variables)**\nToken-related settings combine hardcoded constants with environment variables:\n\n- **Expiry times** (hardcoded constants):\n  ```python\n  ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME = 60 * 30  # 30 minutes in seconds\n  REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME = 60 * 24 * 365  # 365 days in seconds\n  ```\n\n- **JWT configuration** (from environment/constants):\n  ```python\n  SECRET_KEY = environ.get(\"SECRET_KEY\")  # Used for token signing\n  JWT_ALGORITHM = \"HS256\"  # Hardcoded algorithm\n  ```\n\nThe `SECRET_KEY` environment variable is critical for JWT token security, as seen in `auth/services.py` where tokens are created:\n```python\nencoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n    data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n)\n```\n\n## 5. **Redis Configuration**\nRedis settings read from environment variables with fallback defaults:\n```python\nREDIS_HOST = environ.get(\"REDIS_HOST\", \"localhost\")  # Default: \"localhost\"\nREDIS_PORT = environ.get(\"REDIS_PORT\", \"6379\")       # Default: \"6379\"\n```\n\n## 6. **Application Usage**\nThe settings are instantiated as a singleton and imported throughout the application:\n```python\nsettings = Settings()\n```\n\nThis pattern ensures all configuration is centralized, environment-aware, and provides both raw variable access and derived values (like database URLs) for convenience. The template separates concerns: environment variables define infrastructure endpoints, while the Settings class provides a clean API for application code.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1033, "prompt_tokens": 11952, "total_tokens": 12985, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 236, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11392, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0011833212, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002846112, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00089871}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962702-af4ZXfY3UFBE7ITTI3wt", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a6-3356-72e3-ad6d-6ec1d1b1fe84-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11952, "output_tokens": 1033, "total_tokens": 12985, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11392}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 236}}}}]}}}
